cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "Authority Calibration in Long-Horizon AI Agents: A Two-Tailed, Endogeneity-Graded Evaluation Framework"
message: "If you use this framework, the compact paper, or the confidence-bounds code, please cite it."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: "Zavala"
    given-names: "Pablo"
    affiliation: "Block Center for Technology and Society, Carnegie Mellon University"
date-released: "2026-06-17"
version: "0.1.0"
license: MIT
abstract: >-
  A two-tailed (overreach/underreach), endogeneity-graded framework for evaluating AI agents that hold
  operational authority. Failures are scored at the level of concrete state changes in real artifacts rather
  than prose, organized around a latent governance operator that selects a normative frame, decision
  procedure, and reading of the authority structure before acting. This release contains the compact
  submission paper, the conceptual framework, a self-contained confidence-bounds library, and the program's
  ethics and coordinated-disclosure policies. Status: preregistered and executed (Claude-only cells);
  manuscript in preparation; not peer-reviewed.
keywords:
  - AI safety
  - agent evaluation
  - authority calibration
  - oversight allocation
  - responsible disclosure
